kind: llman.sdd.spec
name: "hook-system"
purpose: "TBD - created by archiving change c40-add-hooks. Update purpose after archive."
valid_scope[2]: src/,tests/
requirements[13]{req_id,title,statement}:
  r1,"hook-dispatcher",System MUST implement a HookDispatcher that executes registered hooks for 10+ event types.
  r2,"three-tier-config","System MUST support global/project/user three-tier hook configuration with later layers overriding earlier."
  r3,"script-execution",System MUST execute hook scripts via stdin JSON context and parse stdout for block/allow control.
  h1,"hook-events","Hook system MUST support event types: tool_call (pre/post), model_query (pre), after_provider_request, after_provider_response, turn_end, message_end, compaction, session_start."
  h2,"hook-matching",Hook dispatcher MUST match hooks by event_type.phase.qualifier pattern (e.g. pre.tool_call.bash matches bash tool calls in pre phase).
  h3,"hook-actions","Hook scripts MUST return JSON with action: allow/block/modify; block stops the chain, modify updates args for subsequent hooks."
  h4,"three-tier-hooks","Hook entries MUST merge from three tiers: user > project > global, with same-pattern overrides."
  h5,"hook-timeout","Each hook script MUST execute with a configurable timeout (default 5s), killed if exceeded."
  h6,"hook-env",Hook scripts MUST receive event context as JSON on stdin and inherit configured env vars.
  h7,"prefix-caching-hook","after_provider_request hook MUST allow modifying the provider request payload for prefix-caching optimizations (e.g. deepseek v4 cache_control)."
  h8,"after-provider-response","after_provider_response hook MUST fire after provider responds but before streaming, receiving status and headers."
  h9,"noop-empty","When no hooks are configured, dispatch MUST be a zero-overhead no-op."
  h10,"bdd-hooks",BDD tests under tests/features/hooks.feature MUST all pass.
scenarios[13]{req_id,id,given,when,then}:
  r1,happy,a pre.tool_call hook is registered,tool is about to execute,hook script runs and receives event context via stdin
  r2,happy,global hook and project hook both exist for same event,hook dispatcher runs,project hook overrides global hook
  r3,happy,hook script returns block action,tool execution is pending,tool execution is blocked with reason
  h1,"tool-call-pre",a hook matches pre.tool_call.bash,bash tool is about to execute,hook script receives event JSON on stdin
  h2,"pattern-match","hook entry has events: [\"pre.tool_call.bash\",\"post.step_complete\"]",step_complete event fires in post phase,hook matches
  h3,block,"hook returns {\"action\":\"block\",\"reason\":\"forbidden\"}",dispatch processes result,"DispatchResult::Blocked is returned"
  h4,merge,user config has hook for pre.tool_call overriding global,hooks are loaded,user's hook command is used
  h5,timeout,hook script hangs for 10s with 2s timeout,dispatch waits,"hook is killed and result is Allow (fail-open)"
  h6,env,"hook entry has env: {\"DEBUG\":\"1\"}",hook runs,"the script sees DEBUG=1 in environment\""
  h7,"prefix-cache",after_provider_request hook fires for deepseek model,hook modifies payload,cache_control field is added to request
  h8,"after-response",provider responds with status 200,after_provider_response hook fires,hook receives status=200 and headers
  h9,empty,no hooks are configured,dispatch is called,result is Allowed with zero overhead
  h10,"bdd-pass",BDD runner invoked,"cargo test --test bdd",all hook scenarios pass
